WEBVTT

00:01.084 --> 00:03.295
<i>Previously on "The Rookie"...</i>

00:03.295 --> 00:05.088
Officer Stanton
will be taking over

00:05.088 --> 00:05.881
the training
of Officer West.
Someone broke
into your home?

00:05.881 --> 00:07.216
So, who are you claiming
these days, D?

00:07.216 --> 00:09.009
He did something
that really bothered me.

00:09.009 --> 00:11.595
The way he treated
this one family. Black family.

00:11.595 --> 00:12.804
It's my job to teach you
the right way

00:12.804 --> 00:14.556
to think on the street.

00:14.556 --> 00:16.225
I hear he's a solid cop.

00:16.225 --> 00:18.268
Learn what's useful
and ignore the rest.

00:18.268 --> 00:20.395
Officer Nolan, you will be held
over the FTO program

00:20.395 --> 00:21.647
for an additional month.

00:21.647 --> 00:23.190
Why didn't you tell me?
Why do you think?

00:23.190 --> 00:24.608
Congratulations,
Detective.

00:24.608 --> 00:26.360
Lopez: If I show up pregnant
on day one,

00:26.360 --> 00:27.486
that's all they'll ever
see me as.

00:28.445 --> 00:30.864
[ Cellphone ringing ]

00:30.864 --> 00:33.867
♪♪

00:33.867 --> 00:36.411
Hey! Mom!
Actually, I'm so sorry.

00:36.411 --> 00:38.038
I'm just running
out the door.

00:38.038 --> 00:39.748
<i>Oh, you're always busy.</i>

00:39.748 --> 00:42.251
<i>You haven't been home</i>
<i>in over a year.</i>

00:42.251 --> 00:45.003
Uh, yes, well, rookies still
don't get vacation time, Mom.

00:45.003 --> 00:47.297
You know this.

00:47.297 --> 00:49.675
<i>How about I come for a visit?</i>
<i>Huh?</i>

00:49.675 --> 00:53.095
Uh, well, that would
be...lovely, Mother.

00:53.095 --> 00:54.846
I really don't think
I have the...

00:54.846 --> 00:56.515
time.

00:56.515 --> 01:02.145
Danny had an affair with his ex,
so I dumped him.

01:02.145 --> 01:03.981
I need emotional support.
Emotional support.

01:03.981 --> 01:05.107
Mom, I am so sorry.

01:05.107 --> 01:07.568
He just proposed to you,
though.

01:07.568 --> 01:09.778
I sent flowers.
They're getting delivered today.

01:09.778 --> 01:11.738
Oh, that's so thoughtful
of you.

01:11.738 --> 01:14.032
But I should have known
this was not gonna last.

01:14.032 --> 01:16.827
I told him I wanted
three carats, and apparently,

01:16.827 --> 01:18.495
I'm only worth one
and a quarter.

01:18.495 --> 01:19.538
Uh...
A quarter!

01:19.538 --> 01:21.373
Mother.
[ Sighs ]

01:21.373 --> 01:22.791
You're supposed to give the ring
back when you break up.

01:22.791 --> 01:25.335
[ Scoffs ] Nonsense!
It's damages.

01:25.335 --> 01:28.672
Compensation
for pain and suffering.

01:28.672 --> 01:31.091
And, now, weren't you
in trouble recently?

01:31.091 --> 01:33.719
'Cause Cousin Carol sent me an
article from Facebook or som‐‐

01:33.719 --> 01:35.596
I did not read it.

01:35.596 --> 01:36.972
Your concern is touching.

01:36.972 --> 01:39.182
Um, it's ‐‐
Everything's okay.

01:39.182 --> 01:41.810
I am back on track.
At least I think I am.
Ohh. Oh.

01:41.810 --> 01:44.354
But to that end, I really ‐‐
I can't be late, so I'm ‐‐

01:44.354 --> 01:46.189
Okay, go, go, go.
I'll settle myself in.

01:46.189 --> 01:47.316
Okay.

01:47.316 --> 01:49.109
U‐Uh, actually,
that's my bedroom.

01:49.109 --> 01:50.986
And I'm sure you want your mama
to have it.

01:50.986 --> 01:54.865
♪ Whoa, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh,
oh, oh ♪

01:54.865 --> 01:59.911
♪ I'm gonna win for you
like I know you want me to do ♪

02:03.165 --> 02:04.541
Jackson:
Wanna crash on our couch?

02:04.541 --> 02:07.002
No. Maybe.
I ju‐‐

02:07.002 --> 02:08.670
She's such
an emotional vampire,

02:08.670 --> 02:10.839
and I've got that 30‐day
extension hanging over my head.

02:10.839 --> 02:13.008
I cannot afford to lose focus
right now.

02:13.008 --> 02:14.593
On your six!
Oh!

02:14.593 --> 02:15.969
If I'd have been a banger,
you'd be dead.

02:17.346 --> 02:19.640
I'm not gonna lie.
I'm not fond of him.

02:19.640 --> 02:21.516
Yeah.
Join the club.

02:21.516 --> 02:24.394
[ Sighs ]
I hate training with the public.

02:24.394 --> 02:26.355
I feel like we're sharing
trade secrets.

02:26.355 --> 02:29.900
Is it possible Tim Bradford
is having performance anxiety?

02:29.900 --> 02:31.818
There are pills for that,
you know.

02:31.818 --> 02:34.571
Look, I've come in second behind
Lopez the last four years.

02:34.571 --> 02:36.573
Now that Annie Oakley's
with the detectives,

02:36.573 --> 02:38.283
I got the patrol crown
in the bag.

02:38.283 --> 02:40.744
Oh, there's only one problem
with that.

02:40.744 --> 02:42.037
Me.

02:42.037 --> 02:45.248
Firearm requalification day.

02:45.248 --> 02:47.501
And, yes, I said "day"
because even though

02:47.501 --> 02:50.754
the department allows a month
for you to requalify,

02:50.754 --> 02:54.299
I expect every officer here
to leave with a passing score.

02:54.299 --> 02:57.260
As police officers,
we can never lose sight

02:57.260 --> 02:59.054
of the power we carry
on our hip.

02:59.054 --> 03:01.932
There are only three
circumstances where an officer

03:01.932 --> 03:04.142
should discharge
his or her weapon.

03:04.142 --> 03:05.811
What are they?
Rookies?

03:05.811 --> 03:06.937
To defend
their own life.

03:06.937 --> 03:08.772
To defend
another person's life.

03:08.772 --> 03:10.649
To prevent the escape
of an individual

03:10.649 --> 03:12.776
who's committed a felony
involving the use or threat

03:12.776 --> 03:15.612
of deadly force and poses
an imminent danger to the public

03:15.612 --> 03:17.239
if he or she were allowed
to escape.

03:17.239 --> 03:18.407
Very good.

03:20.826 --> 03:22.994
I'm Officer Dixon,
your Range Master.

03:22.994 --> 03:25.956
Each target has two sides ‐‐
the civilian and the suspect.

03:25.956 --> 03:27.457
When you see the suspect,

03:27.457 --> 03:29.584
you have three seconds
to get shots off.

03:29.584 --> 03:33.088
If you fire on the civilian
side, it is an automatic fail.

03:33.088 --> 03:35.424
[ Gunfire ]

03:35.424 --> 03:37.759
You have 36 shots,
two magazine changes.

03:37.759 --> 03:39.136
30 hits is a pass,
29 a fail.

03:41.430 --> 03:43.181
Whoops.
Almost made somebody an orphan.

03:43.181 --> 03:44.099
Rookies, you're up.

03:45.934 --> 03:47.519
Care to make it
interesting?

03:47.519 --> 03:49.438
20 bucks if your Boot
makes it out on top?

03:49.438 --> 03:50.856
I'll take that bet.

03:50.856 --> 03:52.482
Me, too.

03:52.482 --> 03:54.734
Dixon: Officers ready?
Begin.

03:54.734 --> 03:59.406
[ Gunfire ]

03:59.406 --> 04:01.700
[ Dramatic music plays ]

04:01.700 --> 04:07.205
♪♪

04:07.205 --> 04:12.586
♪♪

04:12.586 --> 04:13.879
Officer Nolan!

04:13.879 --> 04:15.547
[ Gunfire continues ]

04:18.467 --> 04:21.761
So, finishing first with
the most hits, fastest time,

04:21.761 --> 04:23.972
and tightest grouping...

04:23.972 --> 04:26.141
Officer Chen.

04:26.141 --> 04:28.602
Congrats. You are the new
Mid‐Wilshire champ.

04:28.602 --> 04:30.854
[ Cheers and applause ]
Thank you! Thank you.

04:30.854 --> 04:32.898
Thank you very much.

04:32.898 --> 04:35.442
Uh, Bradford, Harper,
you both tied for second.

04:35.442 --> 04:37.277
I don't know
what I hate more ‐‐

04:37.277 --> 04:40.280
tying for second with you
or losing to a rookie.

04:40.280 --> 04:43.658
And in last place,
my only fail in three years ‐‐

04:43.658 --> 04:44.910
Uh, sir, when ‐‐

04:44.910 --> 04:46.453
Officer Nolan,
if I hear one more word

04:46.453 --> 04:48.121
about a guy in scuba gear...
[ Laughter ]

04:48.121 --> 04:50.499
If you don't pass
requalification within 30 days,

04:50.499 --> 04:52.000
you will be put on desk duty

04:52.000 --> 04:53.877
and be given
remedial firearm training.

04:53.877 --> 04:56.171
Is that really the way you want
to end your rookie experience?

04:56.171 --> 04:57.714
No, sir.

04:57.714 --> 05:00.050
Then I suggest
you put in some range time

05:00.050 --> 05:02.219
before your next test.

05:02.219 --> 05:04.679
Alright, see you all
back at the station.

05:09.226 --> 05:10.936
Hey, I need you
to sign this.

05:10.936 --> 05:12.604
Tamara.
Good morning.

05:12.604 --> 05:13.688
Good morning.

05:13.688 --> 05:14.940
Can you sign the title
to the car?

05:14.940 --> 05:16.483
Cops keep eyeballing it,

05:16.483 --> 05:18.026
and they're not gonna believe
you gave it to me.

05:18.026 --> 05:19.402
You know, you still haven't
confirmed

05:19.402 --> 05:21.321
our Tuesday morning appointment
with the social worker.

05:21.321 --> 05:23.031
We need to find you
a real place to live.

05:23.031 --> 05:25.367
I'll be there.
I promise.

05:25.367 --> 05:27.911
Alright.

05:27.911 --> 05:30.247
Oh, hey.
I was a psychology major.

05:30.247 --> 05:32.040
Cool, but it's just a class
that I have to take.

05:32.040 --> 05:34.251
Well, you might want to pay
a little extra attention to it.

05:34.251 --> 05:35.502
I found that
it really helped me

05:35.502 --> 05:37.128
understand
what motivates people.

05:37.128 --> 05:39.256
So does
living on the street.

05:39.256 --> 05:41.883
Fair enough.

05:41.883 --> 05:44.719
[ Pen scratching ]
The car is
officially yours.

05:45.929 --> 05:48.098
Drive safe.
Thanks.

05:48.098 --> 05:49.933
You're welcome.

05:53.353 --> 05:55.981
How's the puppy?
She's doing really great.

05:55.981 --> 05:57.858
Oh, she told me
to tell you, uh,

05:57.858 --> 05:59.359
better luck next time
at the range.

05:59.359 --> 06:01.069
♪♪

06:01.069 --> 06:03.488
Get changed.
Yes, sir.

06:03.488 --> 06:05.657
Dispatcher: <i>7‐Adam‐07,</i>
<i>attach to event 1426...</i>
[ Groans ]

06:05.657 --> 06:07.450
<i>...to assist Homicide</i>
<i>on their 187.</i>

06:07.450 --> 06:08.785
Did you take a look at
that gang book I gave you?

06:08.785 --> 06:10.662
Yes, sir.
It was very informative.

06:10.662 --> 06:12.622
But I don't want to get to a
place where all I see is gangs.

06:12.622 --> 06:14.958
Who's telling you
to do that?

06:14.958 --> 06:17.043
What's the deal?
Homicide.

06:17.043 --> 06:18.879
And, guys,
I gotta run to court.

06:18.879 --> 06:20.297
Detective's en route.

06:20.297 --> 06:21.798
Yeah, no problem.
We'll take over.

06:21.798 --> 06:23.466
Give me some quality
teaching time with the Boot.

06:23.466 --> 06:24.301
Thanks.

06:26.219 --> 06:29.806
Ooh‐ee!
A cholo piñata.

06:29.806 --> 06:31.600
Definitely a gangbanger.

06:31.600 --> 06:33.602
Looks like he got dressed using
the thug life handbook.

06:33.602 --> 06:35.645
What do the tats tell us?

06:35.645 --> 06:38.607
Spider web shows us that he was
caught up in the life.

06:38.607 --> 06:39.900
And the three dots
by his eye?

06:39.900 --> 06:41.860
Stands for
"mi vida loca."

06:41.860 --> 06:44.195
That and the clock tattoo
shows us that he's done time,

06:44.195 --> 06:46.448
and based on the yellow belt
and the bandana,

06:46.448 --> 06:48.491
he probably banged with
Malos Dorados.

06:48.491 --> 06:50.368
Officer West,
I taught you well.

06:50.368 --> 06:51.786
Sorry for making you wait.

06:51.786 --> 06:53.246
Nah, that's a first.

06:53.246 --> 06:55.123
Didn't know detectives
knew the word "sorry."

06:55.123 --> 06:56.583
Well, it wasn't too long ago
I was the one

06:56.583 --> 06:57.959
babysitting
the crime scene.

06:57.959 --> 06:59.628
So, what do we got?

06:59.628 --> 07:02.547
Hispanic male, tortured,
shot execution‐style.

07:02.547 --> 07:04.382
Probably killed
by another gangbanger

07:04.382 --> 07:06.134
whose body we'll find
in an alley next week.

07:06.134 --> 07:09.095
Classic case of No Victims
Involved, if you ask me.

07:09.095 --> 07:11.431
Well, I didn't.

07:11.431 --> 07:12.974
Go start a canvass.

07:12.974 --> 07:14.517
Yes, ma'am.

07:14.517 --> 07:16.645
Mm‐hmm.

07:16.645 --> 07:18.730
Jackson.

07:19.981 --> 07:22.400
Don't let that guy
turn you into a hater.

07:22.400 --> 07:25.070
It's easy to judge,
but this was someone's kid.

07:25.070 --> 07:27.947
I just really miss
riding with you.

07:27.947 --> 07:29.741
Everything okay?

07:29.741 --> 07:31.826
Yeah. You?

07:31.826 --> 07:33.244
Yeah.

07:33.244 --> 07:36.122
[ Police radio chatter ]

07:36.122 --> 07:38.541
Mid‐Wilshire
shooting champ!

07:38.541 --> 07:40.502
I like the sound of that.
Wait, do I get a trophy?

07:40.502 --> 07:41.878
I love trophies.
Relax.

07:41.878 --> 07:43.046
You had
a few good shots.

07:43.046 --> 07:45.256
Come on!
I rocked it!

07:45.256 --> 07:47.008
Don't be salty just because
you got second place.

07:47.008 --> 07:49.094
Plus, you won 40 bucks.
I should get a cut of that.

07:49.094 --> 07:50.887
[ Scoffs ]
Not happening.

07:50.887 --> 07:53.306
But as your T. O., your successes
are my successes.

07:53.306 --> 07:55.266
So you should be thanking me
for training you so well.

07:55.266 --> 07:58.436
[ Chuckling ] Wow.

07:58.436 --> 08:00.355
Isn't that your car?

08:00.355 --> 08:03.608
Yeah, it is.
And he's trying to steal it.

08:03.608 --> 08:05.694
[ Siren chirps ]

08:05.694 --> 08:07.028
[ Groans ]

08:07.028 --> 08:08.488
Sir, step away
from the vehicle.

08:08.488 --> 08:10.240
It's mine.
I just bought it.

08:10.240 --> 08:12.200
But I can't get
this stupid door to open.

08:12.200 --> 08:13.910
What do you mean
you just bought it?

08:13.910 --> 08:16.371
This girl ‐‐ she sold it to me
for 4 grand.

08:16.371 --> 08:19.207
$4,000?!
It's worth at least $10,000!

08:19.207 --> 08:20.917
Okay, $8,000.

08:20.917 --> 08:22.961
Am I in trouble?
No, sir.

08:22.961 --> 08:24.587
Nope.
Sorry to bother you.

08:24.587 --> 08:30.218
♪♪

08:30.218 --> 08:32.762
You ‐‐ You have to push all
the way down before pulling up.

08:34.180 --> 08:36.141
Hey! [ Chuckles ]
Thanks.

08:36.141 --> 08:40.812
♪♪

08:40.812 --> 08:42.564
I should get a do‐over.

08:42.564 --> 08:44.607
I mean, a guy running around
in a scuba suit

08:44.607 --> 08:46.526
and an air tank
at a gun range?

08:46.526 --> 08:48.028
That's weird, right?

08:48.028 --> 08:50.030
Have you never been to
a public range in L. A. before?

08:50.030 --> 08:52.824
It's weird when someone
is <i>not</i> cosplaying.

08:52.824 --> 08:54.784
But you shouldn't have let it
distract you.

08:54.784 --> 08:56.411
You had a gun
in your hand.
N‐‐ I know.
It was just ‐‐

08:56.411 --> 08:58.538
No, no, no, no!
No excuses.

08:58.538 --> 09:01.332
The streets are full
of distractions.

09:01.332 --> 09:04.044
You lose focus,
someone gets killed.

09:04.044 --> 09:05.795
I was really hoping I could
impress Sergeant Grey today.

09:05.795 --> 09:08.006
Yeah, well, you didn't.

09:08.006 --> 09:10.633
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

09:10.633 --> 09:11.926
"Momster"?

09:11.926 --> 09:13.219
I‐I'm sorry.
Do you mind if I...?

09:13.219 --> 09:15.388
Sure. Go ahead.

09:15.388 --> 09:17.265
[ Vibrating continues ]

09:17.265 --> 09:18.892
Hey, Mom, what's up?

09:18.892 --> 09:20.894
Evelyn:
<i>I need directions downtown.</i>

09:20.894 --> 09:23.104
Well, didn't Henry download
that driving app on your phone?

09:23.104 --> 09:25.482
<i>Yes, but it has a very weird</i>
<i>robot voice.</i>

09:25.482 --> 09:27.192
And I've got
impatient son voice.

09:27.192 --> 09:29.903
Use the driving app, Mom.
Bye.

09:29.903 --> 09:30.904
I'm sorry.
That's ‐‐

09:30.904 --> 09:32.864
That's all right.

09:32.864 --> 09:34.657
Look,
when I first joined,

09:34.657 --> 09:36.785
my mom used to call
all the time during shifts.

09:36.785 --> 09:39.496
But eventually,
I just realized that

09:39.496 --> 09:41.998
that was her way
of making sure I was okay.

09:41.998 --> 09:44.417
That's very nice.
This is not that.

09:44.417 --> 09:47.003
Help! Police! Help!
Police!

09:47.003 --> 09:48.463
Police, help!

09:48.463 --> 09:50.799
There's a woman
destroying my house!

09:50.799 --> 09:54.302
♪♪

09:54.302 --> 09:56.096
I ShareBnB the place,

09:56.096 --> 09:58.723
and when I came by to get my
mail, I caught her like this.

09:58.723 --> 10:00.266
You can't make me leave.

10:00.266 --> 10:01.935
Okay, no, w‐we're just
checking to make sure

10:01.935 --> 10:03.186
that everything is okay.

10:03.186 --> 10:05.396
Clearly it's not.
Do something!

10:05.396 --> 10:07.107
Could you get her out of here,
please?

10:07.107 --> 10:09.526
She's ruining Monica's
birth experience.

10:09.526 --> 10:10.693
Um, ma'am, technically,
the young lady

10:10.693 --> 10:12.237
isn't doing anything
illegal.

10:12.237 --> 10:14.864
She's well within her temporary
tenant rights to be here.

10:14.864 --> 10:16.866
And giving birth
really isn't a crime.

10:16.866 --> 10:20.620
It is when it's on my white
European goose downs!

10:20.620 --> 10:21.996
You need to get her out of here,
please.
Yep.

10:21.996 --> 10:23.498
‐No!
‐Ma'am, come with me.

10:23.498 --> 10:24.666
This way. Come on.
[ Monica moaning ]

10:24.666 --> 10:25.792
Hey.
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

10:25.792 --> 10:28.128
Easy. Easy.
You okay?

10:28.128 --> 10:29.546
I'm okay.
Okay.

10:29.546 --> 10:31.047
I'm okay.

10:31.047 --> 10:33.299
I don't like how high
her blood pressure is.

10:33.299 --> 10:37.512
Okay. Um, uh, Monica,
my name is Nyla.

10:37.512 --> 10:39.722
We need to get you
to a hospital.

10:39.722 --> 10:41.558
No, please.

10:41.558 --> 10:43.309
No, no, I don't want to have
my baby at the hospital,

10:43.309 --> 10:44.894
not after what happened
last time.

10:44.894 --> 10:46.479
Please, I don't want to
have my baby at the hospital.

10:46.479 --> 10:48.022
Okay. It's okay.

10:48.022 --> 10:51.317
Listen, I will be with you
the whole way.

10:51.317 --> 10:54.320
♪♪

10:54.320 --> 10:55.780
Monica?

11:02.912 --> 11:04.873
I'm Dr. Kang.
You brought her in?

11:04.873 --> 11:06.332
Yes, sir.
She passed out earlier,

11:06.332 --> 11:07.876
but she came to
in the ambulance.

11:07.876 --> 11:09.460
Who's her OB?

11:09.460 --> 11:12.005
I'm not using one.
I have a doula.

11:12.005 --> 11:13.423
Well, that's not
very smart.

11:13.423 --> 11:14.966
No, it's just that I had

11:14.966 --> 11:16.342
a really bad experience
with my first.

11:16.342 --> 11:18.178
The ‐‐ The cord got twisted,
and the doctor ‐‐

11:18.178 --> 11:19.679
he wouldn't even
check to see ‐‐

11:19.679 --> 11:21.306
Would you please
calm down?

11:21.306 --> 11:22.682
Your blood pressure's
sky‐high,

11:22.682 --> 11:24.434
and getting hysterical
just makes things worse.

11:24.434 --> 11:28.146
Hey, Doc,
this is your patient.

11:28.146 --> 11:31.149
Don't talk down to her.
Just listen.

11:31.149 --> 11:32.817
Can you calm
your partner down?

11:32.817 --> 11:34.819
She's not my partner.
She's my boss.

11:34.819 --> 11:37.071
And she is firing you.

11:37.071 --> 11:38.865
We would like a new doctor,
please.

11:38.865 --> 11:41.034
I'm the head of obstetrics,
and this is not a police matter.

11:44.662 --> 11:47.123
I want a new doctor.

11:47.123 --> 11:50.043
Page me when she
comes to her senses.

11:50.043 --> 11:52.795
I can't do this ‐‐
fighting with doctors again.

11:52.795 --> 11:54.130
T‐They don't want to listen.
They just don't want to listen.

11:54.130 --> 11:55.882
Hey.
We will make them listen.

11:55.882 --> 11:58.885
You got it? Okay?
Me and you. Together.

11:58.885 --> 12:01.012
Who's the doctor
she wants?

12:06.226 --> 12:07.227
Sorry I'm running late.

12:07.227 --> 12:09.145
Just think,
once you retire,

12:09.145 --> 12:10.980
no more schedules,
no more ‐‐

12:10.980 --> 12:12.565
Hey, hey, hey, hey,
hey, hey.

12:12.565 --> 12:14.734
Just keep it down
about those retirement talks.

12:14.734 --> 12:16.486
I haven't told anyone yet.

12:16.486 --> 12:18.655
You having
second thoughts?

12:18.655 --> 12:23.743
No. As soon as I send
this rookie class on their way,

12:23.743 --> 12:26.246
I am all yours.
Oh, well, I like
the sound of that.

12:26.246 --> 12:27.497
You like that?
Alright.

12:27.497 --> 12:29.290
But I‐I was hoping
that we could

12:29.290 --> 12:32.126
look at these together
at lunch.

12:32.126 --> 12:33.753
"Taking Off the Badge:

12:33.753 --> 12:36.422
Retirement Strategies
for Law Enforcement."

12:36.422 --> 12:37.882
Don't laugh.
[ Laughs ]

12:37.882 --> 12:39.467
We both know
the statistics.

12:39.467 --> 12:42.637
Most cops die within
seven years of retirement.

12:42.637 --> 12:44.347
That's not gonna happen.

12:44.347 --> 12:46.724
I know it's not because
I'm not gonna let it.

12:46.724 --> 12:48.309
Luna, how are you?

12:48.309 --> 12:51.145
I'm good,
Detective Lopez.

12:51.145 --> 12:52.272
How you liking
the promotion?

12:52.272 --> 12:54.148
Love it.

12:54.148 --> 12:56.025
Hey, Sarge, I'm working
a weird homicide.

12:56.025 --> 12:58.653
M.E. pulled out silicone‐coated,
armor‐piercing slugs

12:58.653 --> 12:59.696
out of my vic.

12:59.696 --> 13:00.947
Armor‐piercing?

13:00.947 --> 13:02.323
Damn.
Who'd he piss off?

13:02.323 --> 13:03.366
I don't know.

13:03.366 --> 13:05.326
But the guy had ties
to Malos Dorados.

13:05.326 --> 13:06.744
You have a C.I. in still
with them?

13:06.744 --> 13:08.579
Felix Minosa.

13:08.579 --> 13:11.082
But I passed him over to Wysocki
when I became Watch Commander.

13:11.082 --> 13:12.458
He'll hook you up.
Thanks.

13:12.458 --> 13:13.584
Nice seeing you, Luna.

13:13.584 --> 13:14.711
You, too.

13:17.338 --> 13:19.507
You're gonna have to
tell them soon, Wade.

13:19.507 --> 13:21.801
They love you around here.

13:21.801 --> 13:23.636
They're gonna want a chance
to say goodbye.

13:23.636 --> 13:26.639
Still can't believe
how that doctor talked to her.

13:26.639 --> 13:29.142
Oh, there's plenty more
where he came from.

13:29.142 --> 13:30.768
Sounds like you're talking
from experience.

13:30.768 --> 13:34.063
[ Sighs ]
Well, after Lila was born,

13:34.063 --> 13:35.690
I‐I‐I knew
something was wrong,

13:35.690 --> 13:37.984
but the doctor just said
I was being dramatic.

13:37.984 --> 13:42.030
But honestly, if it wasn't
for that nurse...

13:42.030 --> 13:45.158
I‐I will never forget the look
on Donovan's face

13:45.158 --> 13:47.452
when I was being wheeled
into surgery.

13:47.452 --> 13:50.788
He was holding Lila,
and she was just so small and ‐‐

13:50.788 --> 13:52.790
and fragile
and I just ‐‐

13:52.790 --> 13:55.209
I thought I'd never
see them again.

13:55.209 --> 13:57.295
I'm sorry.
You deserved better than that.

13:57.295 --> 13:59.172
Yeah. I did.

13:59.172 --> 14:01.674
Uh, excuse me. Hi.
Yes?

14:01.674 --> 14:03.509
Are you Dr. Peterson?
Yes.

14:03.509 --> 14:05.511
We have a woman
who is in labor,

14:05.511 --> 14:07.055
and she's showing signs
of pre‐eclampsia.

14:07.055 --> 14:09.015
I'm sorry. I already have
a patient in labor.

14:09.015 --> 14:10.308
Now you have two.

14:10.308 --> 14:12.268
Dr. Kang is
the doctor on call.

14:12.268 --> 14:16.522
Would you let Dr. Kang
deliver your baby?

14:16.522 --> 14:17.899
He's my boss.

14:19.776 --> 14:21.694
What room is she in?
She's in 309.

14:21.694 --> 14:22.820
I will introduce you
to her.

14:22.820 --> 14:24.113
[ Cellphone ringing ]
Ah.

14:24.113 --> 14:26.240
Sorry.

14:26.240 --> 14:27.742
Mom, this isn't
a good time.

14:27.742 --> 14:29.952
Evelyn: <i>John, help!</i>
<i>Get away from me!</i>

14:29.952 --> 14:31.454
Mom, what's going on?
Who are you speaking to?

14:31.454 --> 14:33.372
<i>I said get away!</i>
[ <i>Glass breaks</i> ]

14:33.372 --> 14:35.208
[ <i>Line disconnects</i> ]
Mom?

14:35.208 --> 14:36.459
Something's wrong
at my house.

14:36.459 --> 14:37.710
My mom's in trouble.

14:37.710 --> 14:38.628
Take the shop.
Radio for backup.

14:38.628 --> 14:40.421
Right.

14:40.421 --> 14:42.673
♪♪

14:42.673 --> 14:44.592
Hey.

14:44.592 --> 14:46.177
What's going on?
Is my mom okay?

14:46.177 --> 14:47.845
She's a feisty one.

14:47.845 --> 14:49.639
Knows more curse words
than my old drill instructor.

14:49.639 --> 14:51.265
Uh,
who the hell are you?

14:51.265 --> 14:53.351
I'm Danny Hill.
I'm your mom's fiancé.

14:53.351 --> 14:56.646
Ex‐fiancé!
You cheater!

14:56.646 --> 14:58.356
I'm not a cheater.
Evelyn!

14:58.356 --> 15:01.109
Liar!
I had coffee with Pamela

15:01.109 --> 15:03.069
to tell her about
our engagement.

15:03.069 --> 15:05.404
We were married 30 years.
It was the decent thing to do.

15:05.404 --> 15:06.739
I don't believe you.

15:06.739 --> 15:08.449
I don't believe
anything you say.

15:08.449 --> 15:10.409
Will you please leave?

15:10.409 --> 15:12.370
Okay.

15:12.370 --> 15:14.413
Can I just, um,
get the ring back?

15:16.833 --> 15:18.876
I don't have it.

15:18.876 --> 15:20.628
Mom, you showed it to me
this morning.

15:20.628 --> 15:23.214
I know, but it ‐‐ it ‐‐
it was so big

15:23.214 --> 15:24.423
it kept slipping
off my finger.

15:24.423 --> 15:26.175
Maybe it's around here
somewhere.

15:26.175 --> 15:27.802
Mom, just give him back
the ring.

15:27.802 --> 15:29.846
[ Whispering ]
I don't have it.

15:29.846 --> 15:31.430
Is that why
you went downtown today,

15:31.430 --> 15:32.682
so you could sell it
in the diamond district?

15:32.682 --> 15:33.641
Of course not.

15:33.641 --> 15:35.059
Mom.

15:35.059 --> 15:38.146
You barely had it
48 hours.

15:38.146 --> 15:40.565
You never actually intended
to marry me, did you?

15:40.565 --> 15:42.942
You scammed me
for the ring!

15:42.942 --> 15:44.527
Oh, you gold‐digging ‐‐

15:44.527 --> 15:46.821
Yeah, d‐‐

15:46.821 --> 15:47.613
Still my mom.

15:50.324 --> 15:51.868
I want to file
a police report.

15:51.868 --> 15:53.286
[ Chuckles ]
Good luck with that.

15:53.286 --> 15:54.745
That is your right,
sir.

15:54.745 --> 15:56.122
W‐What?
Why are you taking his side?

15:56.122 --> 15:59.750
I'm not.
This is not a costume.

15:59.750 --> 16:02.086
I am a police officer.

16:02.086 --> 16:04.505
Filing a report
is his right.

16:04.505 --> 16:07.633
Betrayed by my own son.

16:10.386 --> 16:12.763
I'm beginning to think
I dodged a bullet.

16:15.766 --> 16:17.393
You gotta be kidding me.

16:17.393 --> 16:20.354
Bad puppy.

16:20.354 --> 16:21.981
You sold my car to
buy new clothes?

16:21.981 --> 16:23.524
And earrings.

16:23.524 --> 16:25.234
It's my car.
You gave it to me.

16:25.234 --> 16:27.570
To sleep in,
not to sell.

16:27.570 --> 16:30.198
Do you have any idea
what it's like to go to school

16:30.198 --> 16:32.909
every day with greasy hair
and dirty clothes?

16:32.909 --> 16:35.203
So, yeah, I sold your
janky‐ass ticket magnet

16:35.203 --> 16:36.787
and bought
a few nice things.

16:36.787 --> 16:38.789
I just want to feel normal
for once.

16:38.789 --> 16:41.125
And so where's the rest
of the money?

16:41.125 --> 16:42.543
It's in my college fund.

16:42.543 --> 16:44.921
Look, why didn't you say
something earlier?

16:44.921 --> 16:47.798
You came by this morning.
You clearly already had a buyer.

16:47.798 --> 16:49.800
I knew you wouldn't
understand.

16:49.800 --> 16:51.636
You would have
just said no.

16:52.803 --> 16:54.972
No. Wait.

16:54.972 --> 16:56.724
Where are you staying?

16:56.724 --> 16:59.101
With my cousin.
Is it safe?

17:00.353 --> 17:02.271
Well...hell!

17:02.271 --> 17:04.732
Dispatcher: <i>All units B. O. L.</i>
<i>211‐armed just occurred.</i>

17:04.732 --> 17:07.985
<i>Suspect is male, Black, 6‐foot,</i>
<i>black pants, blue hoodie.</i>

17:07.985 --> 17:09.111
<i>Weapon a handgun.</i>

17:09.111 --> 17:10.446
Come on.
Let's get to work.

17:13.032 --> 17:15.743
Hey.
There's our guy.

17:15.743 --> 17:17.620
I don't think so.

17:17.620 --> 17:19.872
Uh, the hoodie's green,
not blue.

17:19.872 --> 17:22.500
The suspect is 6 feet.
That guy's too short.

17:22.500 --> 17:24.794
'Cause some scared RP
with a gun in their face

17:24.794 --> 17:27.004
is gonna tell the difference
between green and blue?

17:27.004 --> 17:30.841
6 feet and 5'6"?
Come on.

17:30.841 --> 17:32.426
Control, 7‐Adam‐07,

17:32.426 --> 17:34.971
8th and Bronson,
got a possible 211 suspect.

17:34.971 --> 17:36.264
Code 6.

17:36.264 --> 17:37.598
Here we go.

17:39.016 --> 17:41.185
Hey. LAPD.

17:41.185 --> 17:43.729
Show me your hands.

17:43.729 --> 17:46.232
I said
show me your hands now!
[ <i>Music playing</i>
<i>through headphones</i> ]

17:46.232 --> 17:47.733
[ Kyle groans ]

17:49.193 --> 17:50.528
What the hell?!
Roll over!

17:50.528 --> 17:52.655
I didn't do anything!
I didn't do anything!

17:52.655 --> 17:53.823
Roll over, dumbass!
On your belly!

17:53.823 --> 17:54.865
Aah! I live right here!
[ Grunts ]

17:54.865 --> 17:56.158
Hands behind your back.

17:56.158 --> 17:57.618
Why are you
cuffing me?!

17:57.618 --> 17:58.828
Ow!
For your safety and ours.

17:58.828 --> 18:00.663
My ‐‐ Your ‐‐ My safety?!
Aah!

18:00.663 --> 18:01.956
You're hurting me!
[ Handcuffs click ]

18:01.956 --> 18:03.666
Look, sir, please,
it's gonna be okay.

18:03.666 --> 18:04.959
We just have to
check you out.

18:04.959 --> 18:06.544
Check me out?!
I live right here!

18:06.544 --> 18:08.546
Okay.
What are you doing?!
That's my son!

18:08.546 --> 18:10.089
Ma'am. Ma'am.
Mama, I didn't ‐‐

18:10.089 --> 18:11.299
It's gonna be okay.
It's gonna be okay.

18:11.299 --> 18:12.758
Hey! Back up!
I didn't do nothing.

18:12.758 --> 18:13.968
Let my baby go!
Get off of me!

18:13.968 --> 18:15.636
Lady, I will
knock your ass out!

18:15.636 --> 18:17.972
Get your hands
off my wife!
Are you crazy?!

18:17.972 --> 18:20.391
Control, 7‐Adam‐07, I got
a house emptying out on me.
Son, it's okay.

18:20.391 --> 18:21.851
Send backup.
Let him go!
It's all right, son.

18:21.851 --> 18:23.894
Everybody on the ground!
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

18:23.894 --> 18:26.522
Control, 7‐Adam‐07, we need
a supervisor out here. Code 3.

18:26.522 --> 18:27.940
Everybody,
just stay where you are.

18:27.940 --> 18:30.318
Just ‐‐ Just give us
a minute to explain.

18:30.318 --> 18:32.236
Everybody
on the ground now!

18:32.236 --> 18:33.529
Ronda: I know, I know, baby.
It's okay.

18:33.529 --> 18:36.157
♪♪

18:40.328 --> 18:42.663
[ Siren wailing,
engine revving ]

18:42.663 --> 18:44.874
Shawn: Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Ronda: Baby, you're okay.

18:44.874 --> 18:46.167
Doug: Everyone down
on the ground!

18:46.167 --> 18:48.044
Let him go!
What do you need?

18:48.044 --> 18:49.962
Help Jackson
hook these idiots up.

18:49.962 --> 18:51.380
We're arresting
the whole family?

18:51.380 --> 18:52.965
What the hell
did I just say?

18:52.965 --> 18:55.551
Wait,
even the grandmother?

18:55.551 --> 18:57.136
Are you serious?

18:57.136 --> 18:59.180
Alright, West, Chen,
you stay here.

18:59.180 --> 19:00.640
Stanton, come here.
Let's go sort this out.

19:00.640 --> 19:02.391
Woman: Hey, I'm recording this.
I see you.

19:02.391 --> 19:03.643
Man: It's always the same
with you guys.

19:03.643 --> 19:05.394
Get those cuffs
off my boy!

19:05.394 --> 19:07.146
We can't, ma'am.
Not yet, anyways.

19:07.146 --> 19:08.272
It's protocol.
I'm sorry.

19:08.272 --> 19:10.232
Not as sorry as this
fake‐ass brother.

19:10.232 --> 19:12.151
Uncle Tom sellout.

19:12.151 --> 19:14.987
We spotted the 211 suspect,
ordered him to stop.

19:14.987 --> 19:16.280
H‐Hold up, hold up.

19:16.280 --> 19:17.323
They ‐‐ They just
pinched that guy

19:17.323 --> 19:19.200
half a mile from here
two minutes ago.

19:19.200 --> 19:20.076
You didn't hear that
on the radio?

19:22.203 --> 19:23.663
I'm arresting
all of them.

19:23.663 --> 19:25.247
Attempted assault
on a police officer,

19:25.247 --> 19:26.916
resisting arrest,
criminal threats.

19:26.916 --> 19:29.001
What are you doing here?
There are cameras all around.

19:29.001 --> 19:31.545
You nabbed an innocent man.
The D. A. won't file.

19:31.545 --> 19:33.589
These people
don't respect authority.

19:33.589 --> 19:35.508
You grabbed the wrong guy.

19:35.508 --> 19:37.802
You're senior officer.

19:37.802 --> 19:38.928
It's your call.

19:38.928 --> 19:41.430
[ Siren wailing ]

19:41.430 --> 19:43.557
Control,
7‐Adam‐19, Code 4.

19:43.557 --> 19:45.851
Shut down Code 3 units
and cancel the supervisor.

19:45.851 --> 19:47.186
Jackson, come here.

19:47.186 --> 19:49.271
Uncuff that gentleman
with an apology.

19:49.271 --> 19:50.648
Talk to the family,
explain the situation.

19:50.648 --> 19:52.441
See if you can
dust them off, okay?

19:52.441 --> 19:53.734
Okay.
I'll join you
in a minute.

19:53.734 --> 19:55.277
And now you're gonna
kiss their ass?

19:55.277 --> 19:56.445
It's called
the least we can do.

19:58.239 --> 20:00.616
Woman: It's not right.
That's not right.

20:00.616 --> 20:02.827
Man:
He should lock him up.
Finally.

20:02.827 --> 20:06.414
Uh, sir, I am ‐‐ I'm truly sorry
for the, uh, confusion.

20:06.414 --> 20:08.791
Confusion?
You just cuffed my grandbaby

20:08.791 --> 20:10.835
and pointed guns
at my entire family.

20:10.835 --> 20:12.503
And we're very sorry,
ma'am.

20:12.503 --> 20:14.839
Look, ma'am,
we were looking for a suspect

20:14.839 --> 20:16.340
that fit the description
of your grandson.

20:16.340 --> 20:18.300
Oh!
Yeah. Young and Black.

20:18.300 --> 20:20.511
We need to
speak to your Sergeant.
Tim: Of course.

20:20.511 --> 20:22.096
Ma'am,
here's my business card

20:22.096 --> 20:23.764
in case you want to
file a complaint.

20:23.764 --> 20:24.974
You bet your ass we do.

20:28.602 --> 20:30.438
Hey.
It's a girl.

20:30.438 --> 20:33.107
[ Chuckles ] Mother and daughter
are doing just fine.

20:33.107 --> 20:35.609
That's great.
What happened with your mom?

20:35.609 --> 20:38.904
Oh, it's just a hot mess,
which is normal.

20:38.904 --> 20:40.531
Fiancé flew in
to win her back.

20:40.531 --> 20:42.116
She'd already
hocked the engagement ring,

20:42.116 --> 20:45.286
so he filed a police report,
with me, which I'll hear about.

20:45.286 --> 20:47.496
I just wish I could say
this was new behavior,

20:47.496 --> 20:49.707
but she's been pulling this
love‐'em‐and‐leave‐'em stuff

20:49.707 --> 20:51.834
since my dad split.

20:51.834 --> 20:54.962
Well, not like I'm trying to
defend her or anything,

20:54.962 --> 20:59.133
but a single mom raising a kid
alone in the '60s ‐‐

20:59.133 --> 21:00.885
'80s.

21:00.885 --> 21:03.220
Late '70s, early '80s.

21:03.220 --> 21:04.764
Whatever.

21:04.764 --> 21:07.683
Women couldn't even get their
own credit cards back then.

21:07.683 --> 21:11.937
I mean, society was designed to
make them depend on men.

21:11.937 --> 21:15.816
So maybe that made your mom
a little...mercenary.

21:18.235 --> 21:20.029
Lopez:
Your old C.I. came through.

21:20.029 --> 21:21.822
What did Felix tell you?
That my murder victim
was recruited

21:21.822 --> 21:23.783
to be local muscle
for a Guatemalan cartel,

21:23.783 --> 21:25.951
specifically for
La Fiera.

21:25.951 --> 21:28.913
La Fiera?
It's a woman?

21:28.913 --> 21:30.498
Her real name's
Sandra de la Cruz.

21:30.498 --> 21:32.666
She's a big‐time drug runner
from Guatemala.

21:32.666 --> 21:34.210
Legend goes that
when she was only 15,

21:34.210 --> 21:35.753
she was walking home
from the hospital

21:35.753 --> 21:37.880
with her newborn son
when she got caught

21:37.880 --> 21:40.466
in the crossfire
between two rival gangs.

21:40.466 --> 21:43.177
To protect her baby,
she picks up a semiautomatic

21:43.177 --> 21:45.763
off a dead narco
and kills everyone.

21:45.763 --> 21:48.766
The cartel was so impressed,
they recruited her

21:48.766 --> 21:51.519
and named her La Fiera.
And you believe that?

21:51.519 --> 21:54.522
There's songs written about it
and a kick‐ass telenovela.

21:54.522 --> 21:56.899
So, whether her origin story
is true or not,

21:56.899 --> 22:00.194
La Fiera is very real
and very dangerous.

22:00.194 --> 22:02.613
And you think she's connected
to your homicide?

22:02.613 --> 22:05.533
I don't know.

22:05.533 --> 22:06.826
What are these?

22:08.994 --> 22:10.454
You're putting in
your papers?

22:10.454 --> 22:11.664
When?

22:11.664 --> 22:13.624
I don't know.

22:13.624 --> 22:16.043
Were you gonna
say something?

22:16.043 --> 22:19.547
Like you share all
your personal decisions?

22:19.547 --> 22:20.714
Eventually.

22:20.714 --> 22:22.424
Exactly.

22:22.424 --> 22:24.343
I'll tell everyone
when I'm ready.

22:24.343 --> 22:25.594
Yes, sir.

22:25.594 --> 22:27.596
I'm happy for you.

22:27.596 --> 22:30.724
I just...

22:30.724 --> 22:32.142
It won't be
the same without you.

22:34.603 --> 22:37.189
Well, I'm either going to the
range or home to my mother.

22:37.189 --> 22:38.983
So, you're going
to the range?

22:38.983 --> 22:40.651
100%.
Maybe even a late dinner?

22:40.651 --> 22:43.320
You know, you could always
ask her to get a hotel.

22:43.320 --> 22:44.697
You know, you'd think
that'd be the case.

22:44.697 --> 22:46.240
Doug: You broke the first rule
of being a cop ‐‐

22:46.240 --> 22:48.033
have your fellow officer's
back.

22:48.033 --> 22:50.327
I did.
You questioned
every move I made,

22:50.327 --> 22:52.329
all before the suspects
were even in cuffs.

22:52.329 --> 22:54.748
But what really pissed me off ‐‐
calling for a supervisor.

22:54.748 --> 22:57.042
The whole city hears that and
thinks we're in over our heads.

22:57.042 --> 22:58.043
We were in
over our heads!

22:58.043 --> 22:59.879
No, you were!

22:59.879 --> 23:01.881
Don't let it happen again.

23:04.049 --> 23:06.176
Hey. Was he actually giving you
a hard time

23:06.176 --> 23:07.928
about today?
Yeah, it's whatever.

23:07.928 --> 23:09.305
I just have to hold it down
for a few more weeks

23:09.305 --> 23:11.181
then I'll be free of him.
What happened?

23:11.181 --> 23:13.642
He jacked up the wrong suspect,
then threatened the family.

23:13.642 --> 23:16.770
A Black family,
and it's not the first time.

23:16.770 --> 23:19.106
You should tell Grey.
Or at least
talk to Tim about it.

23:19.106 --> 23:20.733
I did already.

23:20.733 --> 23:22.985
Tim said that he heard Doug
was "a solid cop,"

23:22.985 --> 23:25.070
and that I should,
"learn what's useful from him

23:25.070 --> 23:26.238
and ignore the rest."

23:26.238 --> 23:28.866
He said that?
Yeah.

23:28.866 --> 23:31.577
And, look,
as horrible as today was,

23:31.577 --> 23:33.954
technically,
Stanton didn't break any laws.

23:33.954 --> 23:36.624
Plus, he's an 11‐year vet
and I'm just a rookie.

23:36.624 --> 23:38.125
No one's
gonna listen to me.

23:38.125 --> 23:39.919
We're listening.

23:39.919 --> 23:42.046
And we're here if you ever want
to talk about it.

23:44.006 --> 23:45.007
Thank you.

23:55.142 --> 23:59.021
[ Pink Frost's
"New Minds" plays ]

23:59.021 --> 24:01.023
♪ I see the wrecking ♪

24:01.023 --> 24:03.692
♪ I see the rain ♪

24:03.692 --> 24:05.903
♪ I see the way now ♪

24:05.903 --> 24:07.863
♪ I see the way ‐‐ ♪

24:07.863 --> 24:08.989
[ Music stops ]

24:15.704 --> 24:17.623
Excuse me.
Hate to bother you.

24:17.623 --> 24:20.084
I saw you on the range earlier.
I'm with the LAPD.

24:20.084 --> 24:22.252
[ Gunfire ]

24:22.252 --> 24:23.796
♪♪

24:23.796 --> 24:25.547
[ Engine starts ]

24:25.547 --> 24:30.886
♪♪

24:35.099 --> 24:37.309
Hey. I just heard.
You all right?

24:37.309 --> 24:38.686
Yeah, yeah.
My truck, not so much.

24:38.686 --> 24:40.437
Any idea
who the shooter is?

24:40.437 --> 24:42.481
No, not yet.
I did get a look at him, though.

24:42.481 --> 24:44.233
He was at the firing range
during our qualifications,

24:44.233 --> 24:45.609
wearing a full scuba suit.

24:45.609 --> 24:47.736
Who's the
investigating detective?

24:47.736 --> 24:49.697
Uh, actually,
it looks like it's you.

24:49.697 --> 24:51.615
Crime scene techs identified
the shooter's ammunition ‐‐

24:51.615 --> 24:53.450
silicone‐covered,
armor‐piercing.

24:53.450 --> 24:55.077
Same as my homicide.

24:55.077 --> 24:56.996
And then the suspect got away
in a white sedan,

24:56.996 --> 24:58.497
but I only got
a partial plate.

24:58.497 --> 25:00.541
Luckily, that was all we needed.
So, we've got five possibles.

25:00.541 --> 25:02.334
Only one
was a white sedan.

25:02.334 --> 25:04.253
It's a rental out
of Pico‐Union.
You get a name?

25:04.253 --> 25:06.714
Yes, they e‐mailed us
a copy of his driver's license.

25:06.714 --> 25:08.841
Guillermo Sandoval.

25:08.841 --> 25:10.217
That's him.
This is the guy.

25:12.344 --> 25:13.846
He's definitely connected
to my murder.

25:13.846 --> 25:15.973
Victim worked for
a Guatemalan cartel.

25:15.973 --> 25:17.850
Any idea
where this guy is now?
Actually, yeah.

25:17.850 --> 25:19.184
We got a hit off
of his credit card

25:19.184 --> 25:20.561
that he used for
the rent‐a‐car.

25:20.561 --> 25:22.771
It's, uh, one of those
no‐tell motels on Ventura.

25:22.771 --> 25:25.566
I'll call for a warrant.

25:25.566 --> 25:27.484
[ Lopez speaking Spanish ]
[ Banging on door ]

25:30.654 --> 25:32.156
I got him! Got him!

25:32.156 --> 25:33.365
Show me your hands.

25:33.365 --> 25:35.117
[ Cellphone chimes ]
Out here. Nice and slow.

25:35.117 --> 25:36.577
Out here.
On your knees.

25:36.577 --> 25:38.746
Give me that.
Hands on your head.

25:38.746 --> 25:40.748
He just sent a text.

25:40.748 --> 25:41.915
Lopez:
"Policía. Plan B."

25:43.709 --> 25:48.630
♪♪

25:48.630 --> 25:49.882
He's a cop.

25:56.847 --> 25:58.432
<i>At first,</i>
<i>it didn't make sense to me</i>

25:58.432 --> 26:01.393
how a cop with a good reputation
could do this.

26:01.393 --> 26:02.853
Then I did
a little research.

26:02.853 --> 26:05.064
You survived
the Massacre of Antiguo Leon.

26:05.064 --> 26:06.899
Your village stood up
to the cartel,

26:06.899 --> 26:08.358
and they were slaughtered.

26:08.358 --> 26:12.404
Men, women, children...
your children.

26:12.404 --> 26:14.782
But this man
that you tortured and killed

26:14.782 --> 26:16.241
had nothing to do
with that.

26:16.241 --> 26:18.160
He worked for the one
who ordered it done.

26:19.870 --> 26:21.955
La Fiera.

26:21.955 --> 26:24.833
And you want revenge,
but she's a hard one to catch.

26:24.833 --> 26:27.044
Smart and very cautious.

26:27.044 --> 26:30.297
<i>Rumor is she only travels</i>
<i>by yacht to avoid ambush.</i>

26:30.297 --> 26:33.467
So...that explains
the scuba gear.

26:33.467 --> 26:36.220
You needed to practice shooting
with all that equipment on.

26:36.220 --> 26:38.347
Clearly,
that was Plan "A."

26:38.347 --> 26:41.850
But you sent someone a text
ordering Plan "B."

26:41.850 --> 26:43.852
So, what is that?

26:43.852 --> 26:46.814
You'll find out...
soon enough.

26:49.483 --> 26:51.985
Yeah, well,
thanks for nothing.

26:51.985 --> 26:54.947
My guy at the DEA didn't even
know La Fiera was in town.

26:54.947 --> 26:56.990
That's more than
a little scary.

26:56.990 --> 26:58.992
And it's so strange to think
that if I hadn't been distracted

26:58.992 --> 27:01.161
by a guy in a scuba suit
at a gun range,

27:01.161 --> 27:03.956
there would be a bloodbath
on a yacht right now.

27:03.956 --> 27:05.833
Yeah,
that was a good spot.

27:05.833 --> 27:07.751
Not what
you said yesterday.

27:07.751 --> 27:10.045
But who's keeping score?

27:10.045 --> 27:11.922
Clearly, you.
Clearly.

27:11.922 --> 27:13.590
I hope Grey is,
too, though.

27:13.590 --> 27:15.467
You think there's any way he
would be so impressed by this,

27:15.467 --> 27:17.886
he might, you know,
let me off the hook

27:17.886 --> 27:18.971
for that 30‐day
extension?

27:20.597 --> 27:23.350
Officer Nolan,

27:23.350 --> 27:25.769
why were you given
an official letter of reprimand

27:25.769 --> 27:28.480
and extended in
the FTO program?

27:28.480 --> 27:30.357
Because I ignored
an LAPD regulation.

27:30.357 --> 27:31.984
Among other things.

27:31.984 --> 27:34.194
And do you feel that that was
a fitting punishment,

27:34.194 --> 27:35.821
considering
your violation?

27:35.821 --> 27:38.240
Yes.

27:38.240 --> 27:40.617
And yet you want
special treatment.

27:40.617 --> 27:43.954
When we pinch someone breaking
the law, they are punished.

27:43.954 --> 27:45.330
If those rules
apply to them,

27:45.330 --> 27:48.292
then they absolutely
apply to us, as well.

27:48.292 --> 27:50.294
[ Door opens ]
La Fiera's in town with her son

27:50.294 --> 27:52.129
for a college tour.

27:52.129 --> 27:53.964
They're gonna kill her
on campus.

27:53.964 --> 27:56.174
[ Rapping ] ♪ Ice tunnel
when the pressure closes ♪

27:56.174 --> 27:57.676
So, now we have to
protect a drug lord?

27:57.676 --> 27:59.136
Can't we just
take an early lunch

27:59.136 --> 28:00.512
and let nature
take its course?

28:00.512 --> 28:01.889
Any real questions?

28:01.889 --> 28:03.807
Anyone have a case on her?
DEA? FBI?

28:03.807 --> 28:05.183
She's on
everyone's radars,

28:05.183 --> 28:06.810
but there's no open warrants
in the US.

28:06.810 --> 28:08.103
So as far as we're concerned,
she's clean.

28:08.103 --> 28:09.438
Think she has
private security?

28:09.438 --> 28:10.939
Definitely.
And they'll be packing.

28:10.939 --> 28:12.524
Let's pray we get there before
the trouble starts.

28:12.524 --> 28:15.736
[ Rapping ]
♪ Walk out with adrenaline ♪

28:15.736 --> 28:17.946
♪ So cold‐blooded ♪

28:17.946 --> 28:19.823
Guy: Mom, wait up.

28:19.823 --> 28:22.159
♪ Ah, ah ♪

28:22.159 --> 28:23.827
Chen:
Can you believe Stanton?

28:23.827 --> 28:26.371
"Can't we just let nature
run its natural course?"

28:26.371 --> 28:29.416
Really? No comment?
None at all?

28:29.416 --> 28:30.876
Look, he's not
my favorite cop, either,

28:30.876 --> 28:32.586
especially after
he handled that family.

28:32.586 --> 28:34.504
You mean the way
he terrorized them?

28:34.504 --> 28:36.924
Look, I've been around guys
like Doug my entire career,

28:36.924 --> 28:38.884
military and police.

28:38.884 --> 28:40.844
They're rough around
the edges.

28:40.844 --> 28:43.013
"Rough around the edges,"
"old school," "hard‐charging."

28:43.013 --> 28:45.515
Come on, man.
Stanton is a racist.

28:45.515 --> 28:48.477
You don't know that for sure.
Uh, yeah, actually, I do.

28:48.477 --> 28:52.105
But you're right.
Let's just make excuses for him.

28:52.105 --> 28:54.274
Phew!
This place is something else.

28:54.274 --> 28:56.068
A lot nicer
than where I went.

28:56.068 --> 28:58.946
Chico State.
Where'd you go?

28:58.946 --> 29:01.698
UCLA.
Ah!

29:01.698 --> 29:03.575
Too short
for basketball.

29:03.575 --> 29:05.243
So football?

29:05.243 --> 29:06.954
Come on, you played,
didn't you?

29:06.954 --> 29:08.372
Knew it.

29:08.372 --> 29:10.499
What is that
supposed to mean?

29:10.499 --> 29:13.043
I also had a 4.4 GPA, and I was
valedictorian of my class,

29:13.043 --> 29:15.128
if you were wondering
how I got in.

29:15.128 --> 29:18.715
I wasn't.
♪ Ah, ah ♪

29:18.715 --> 29:22.344
♪ So cold‐blooded ♪

29:22.344 --> 29:24.137
♪ Ah ♪
♪ So cold‐blooded ♪

29:24.137 --> 29:26.890
It's the perfect combo
of hard work and fun.

29:26.890 --> 29:29.309
All units. Found them.

29:29.309 --> 29:31.561
Lopez, Humanities building,
east entrance.

29:31.561 --> 29:34.064
This campus is mad lit.
[ Chuckles ]

29:40.487 --> 29:43.240
Yes, what can I do for you,
Detective?

29:43.240 --> 29:46.076
You may speak freely in front of
my son. I hide nothing from him.

29:46.076 --> 29:47.828
There's a credible threat
against your life.

29:47.828 --> 29:51.248
I have officers ready to escort
you to a safe location.

29:51.248 --> 29:53.333
It's okay.
[ Velcro ripping ]

29:53.333 --> 29:55.711
♪♪

29:55.711 --> 29:56.837
Just as a precaution.

29:59.172 --> 30:00.757
Man: La Fiera!

30:00.757 --> 30:02.426
Get down!
[ Gunfire ]

30:02.426 --> 30:04.052
Go! Run!

30:04.052 --> 30:05.053
[ People screaming ]
Look out!

30:09.516 --> 30:11.184
Go! Go! Run!

30:11.184 --> 30:13.895
[ Gunfire ]
[ People screaming ]

30:13.895 --> 30:16.857
All units,
I'm taking rifle rounds.

30:16.857 --> 30:18.316
Humanities building,
third floor.

30:18.316 --> 30:20.068
[ Gunfire ]

30:20.068 --> 30:22.070
Diamond formation
when we get inside, got it?

30:22.070 --> 30:23.822
I'll provide
cover fire.

30:23.822 --> 30:25.032
Alright,
time to run like hell.

30:25.032 --> 30:27.743
Ready?
Three, two, one, go.

30:27.743 --> 30:34.291
♪♪

30:34.291 --> 30:40.589
♪♪

30:40.589 --> 30:42.632
[ Gunfire ]

30:49.806 --> 30:53.810
[ Gunfire in distance ]

30:53.810 --> 30:55.729
Who is it?
Who's after me?

30:55.729 --> 30:57.814
I can't tell you that.

30:57.814 --> 30:59.483
He's arrested, no?

30:59.483 --> 31:01.026
There'll be a record.
I'll find out anyway.

31:01.026 --> 31:02.360
So why not
just give me his name?

31:02.360 --> 31:04.112
'Cause of what you might
do to him.

31:11.828 --> 31:13.705
I thought that you didn't
hide anything from your son,

31:13.705 --> 31:15.332
"La Fiera."

31:15.332 --> 31:18.126
I like you.
A strong <i>hermana.</i>

31:18.126 --> 31:20.962
But I am just
a businesswoman.

31:20.962 --> 31:22.422
Businesswomen don't have
<i>narcocorridos</i>

31:22.422 --> 31:24.674
written about them.
Please.

31:24.674 --> 31:26.301
People in my country,
they like to tell stories,

31:26.301 --> 31:28.220
create legends.

31:28.220 --> 31:30.013
Doesn't make them
all true.

31:30.013 --> 31:32.390
Nolan: <i>Lopez, 7‐Adam‐15.</i>
<i>Shots fired. West stairwell.</i>

31:32.390 --> 31:33.725
<i>Pursuing suspect towards roof.</i>

31:33.725 --> 31:35.435
Copy that.

31:35.435 --> 31:37.437
It's killing you, eh?

31:37.437 --> 31:39.064
That you can't be out there
in the action?

31:39.064 --> 31:41.108
I'm protecting you.
No.

31:41.108 --> 31:43.318
You're protecting
your <i>criatura.</i>

31:43.318 --> 31:45.612
You're pregnant, no?
I can tell.

31:45.612 --> 31:47.280
Diego gave me
awful heartburn, too.

31:47.280 --> 31:49.908
What? No.
Hey, come on, <i>hermana.</i>

31:49.908 --> 31:51.952
We're not sisters.

31:51.952 --> 31:54.538
Do you know why
they call me "La Fiera"?

31:54.538 --> 31:57.290
You were caught in a narco
gunfight with baby Diego.

31:57.290 --> 31:59.459
You grabbed a gun and laid
everyone to waste.

31:59.459 --> 32:01.586
[ Scoffs ]
Sounds more legend than truth.

32:01.586 --> 32:02.963
No.

32:02.963 --> 32:06.091
That story is all truth.

32:06.091 --> 32:08.510
We're survivors,
Diego and me.

32:08.510 --> 32:12.597
When it comes to your child,
there is nothing you won't do,

32:12.597 --> 32:17.394
nothing you won't become
to protect them.

32:17.394 --> 32:19.312
You'll see.

32:19.312 --> 32:22.649
[ Sirens wailing ]

32:22.649 --> 32:25.360
[ Loud whirring ]

32:36.746 --> 32:39.082
[ Whirring continues ]

32:46.756 --> 32:48.967
[ Gunfire ]

32:48.967 --> 32:55.182
♪♪

32:55.182 --> 33:01.479
♪♪

33:01.479 --> 33:04.441
Aah!
Ohh! Ohh!

33:04.441 --> 33:10.363
♪♪

33:10.363 --> 33:16.244
♪♪

33:16.244 --> 33:18.371
Get down
on the ground now!

33:18.371 --> 33:20.207
<i>Ponte en el suelo!</i>

33:20.207 --> 33:28.131
♪♪

33:28.131 --> 33:29.633
[ Body thuds ]

33:29.633 --> 33:37.390
♪♪

33:37.390 --> 33:45.232
♪♪

33:45.232 --> 33:47.734
The State Department's
satisfied with your statement.

33:47.734 --> 33:51.404
You can go.
<i>Ay, muchas gracias,</i>
Detective.

33:51.404 --> 33:54.741
Diego,
he likes this school.

33:54.741 --> 33:57.661
So, who knows?
Maybe we'll see you around.

33:57.661 --> 33:59.871
[ Velcro rips ]

34:03.583 --> 34:05.168
Don't mistake
the professionalism

34:05.168 --> 34:07.212
I showed you today
for weakness.

34:07.212 --> 34:09.172
Loving your son
doesn't excuse you

34:09.172 --> 34:10.548
from the crimes
you've committed.

34:10.548 --> 34:12.509
You come back to L. A. when
there's a charge on your head,

34:12.509 --> 34:15.178
I'll put
the cuffs on myself.

34:15.178 --> 34:17.973
I would expect nothing less,
<i>hermana.</i>

34:25.605 --> 34:28.108
Officer West.
I'm on my way out.

34:28.108 --> 34:29.276
Can this wait
till the morning?

34:29.276 --> 34:31.069
Uh, no, sir.
This ‐‐ This can't.

34:31.069 --> 34:34.489
[ Sighs ]
Alright, come on.

34:34.489 --> 34:37.409
It's, um ‐‐
It's Officer Stanton.

34:37.409 --> 34:41.871
He, um ‐‐
He's a bad cop, sir.

34:41.871 --> 34:44.124
In what way?

34:44.124 --> 34:47.085
To be honest,
every way.

34:47.085 --> 34:49.462
Who he chooses
to pull over,

34:49.462 --> 34:51.840
how he ‐‐ how he treats suspects
of color,

34:51.840 --> 34:52.841
the things he says.

34:52.841 --> 34:54.551
Give me specifics.

34:54.551 --> 34:57.262
Saying that a crime has
"no victims involved"

34:57.262 --> 34:59.389
just because the deceased
was affiliated.

34:59.389 --> 35:03.268
Look, a lot of cops
feel that way.

35:03.268 --> 35:04.894
It's an attitude
I don't agree with,

35:04.894 --> 35:06.771
but it doesn't violate
any rules.

35:06.771 --> 35:08.982
I‐It's not just that,
sir.

35:08.982 --> 35:10.609
Y‐Yesterday we
felony‐stopped a man

35:10.609 --> 35:12.694
who did not fit
the suspect description.

35:17.782 --> 35:18.908
He was outside
of his own home.

35:18.908 --> 35:20.619
I know about that.
I read the report.

35:20.619 --> 35:22.787
Did you check the body cams?
Beca‐‐

35:22.787 --> 35:25.582
Stanton wanted to arrest
this guy's entire family, sir.

35:25.582 --> 35:27.500
Last I checked,

35:27.500 --> 35:29.836
it's within cops' discretion
to make arrests.

35:29.836 --> 35:31.713
It was unwarranted, sir!

35:31.713 --> 35:34.049
Look, Stanton escalated
the entire situation

35:34.049 --> 35:35.759
to the point where it became
dangerous for both us

35:35.759 --> 35:37.510
and that man's family.
[ Door opens ]

35:37.510 --> 35:39.554
Bradford, we're in the middle
of something, so ‐‐

35:39.554 --> 35:41.389
I‐I think I know
what it's about.

35:41.389 --> 35:44.643
Look, whatever Officer West is
telling you, I stand with him.

35:50.357 --> 35:52.400
Fine.

35:52.400 --> 35:54.569
I'll put Stanton on the desk
till we figure it out.

35:54.569 --> 35:56.571
With all due respect, sir,
that is not good enough.

35:56.571 --> 35:58.698
Jackson.

35:58.698 --> 36:01.368
Excuse me, son?

36:01.368 --> 36:03.745
You've been on the job
for five minutes.

36:03.745 --> 36:06.247
I've got 25 years.

36:06.247 --> 36:08.208
You don't know what
I had to put up with,

36:08.208 --> 36:11.211
what your father had to put up
with to get this far.

36:11.211 --> 36:13.421
You stand
on our shoulders.

36:13.421 --> 36:16.800
And yet the water is still
above my head.

36:16.800 --> 36:19.552
So, tell me this, sir.

36:19.552 --> 36:22.180
What were
all your sacrifices for?

36:24.933 --> 36:28.019
Get the hell
out of my office, West.

36:33.900 --> 36:35.568
Look, I know you're pissed.
Why aren't you?

36:35.568 --> 36:37.237
I am.
It's just...

36:37.237 --> 36:39.030
I've been making excuses
for pricks like Stanton

36:39.030 --> 36:41.241
my entire life, figured
there was no changing them,

36:41.241 --> 36:43.326
so I'd let it go,
I gave them a pass.

36:43.326 --> 36:46.496
It wasn't a pass.
You gave them permission.

36:46.496 --> 36:48.581
Silence is complicity,
sir.

36:48.581 --> 36:50.625
Yeah.

36:50.625 --> 36:51.751
I get that now.

36:51.751 --> 36:53.503
But Sarge is right.

36:53.503 --> 36:56.631
Benching Stanton is the only
recourse he has.

36:56.631 --> 36:58.007
It's not good enough.

36:58.007 --> 37:02.053
♪ Come back home ♪

37:02.053 --> 37:07.183
♪ Come back home ♪

37:07.183 --> 37:09.978
♪ Back to these open arms
where you belong ♪
Can you page Officer Chen?

37:09.978 --> 37:11.354
Tamara.
Hey.

37:11.354 --> 37:13.523
Hey!

37:13.523 --> 37:16.276
♪ Come back home ♪
Look.

37:16.276 --> 37:18.820
I don't trust people
who are nice to me.

37:18.820 --> 37:21.531
♪ You know I've been waiting,
waiting for so long ♪
Yeah, I get it.

37:21.531 --> 37:24.993
Look, predators are everywhere,
especially on the street.

37:24.993 --> 37:27.162
Trust is something that needs to
be earned, not bought.

37:27.162 --> 37:30.707
So, how can I
earn trust with you?

37:30.707 --> 37:33.001
Well, according
to my psychology textbook,

37:33.001 --> 37:34.878
there are
seven different ways

37:34.878 --> 37:36.171
to build trust
in a relationship.

37:36.171 --> 37:37.547
Mm‐hmm.

37:37.547 --> 37:39.883
And if memory serves,
I believe they boil down to

37:39.883 --> 37:41.885
doing what you say
you're going to.

37:41.885 --> 37:43.762
Exactly.

37:43.762 --> 37:47.682
Um, I need a safe place
to keep this at night.

37:47.682 --> 37:49.309
[ Bag unzips ]

37:49.309 --> 37:51.644
It's the first computer
I've ever owned.

37:51.644 --> 37:53.521
♪ Come back home ♪

37:53.521 --> 37:55.732
Uh, I used to do all my school
work on the one at the library,

37:55.732 --> 37:57.358
but it's like
a hundred years old.

37:57.358 --> 37:59.903
And your cousin's
is not a safe place?

37:59.903 --> 38:01.738
It's safe‐adjacent.

38:01.738 --> 38:03.865
I mean, I won't get attacked
while I'm asleep,

38:03.865 --> 38:06.701
but this will get pawned
in five seconds.

38:06.701 --> 38:09.746
You can pick this up here
every morning before school.

38:09.746 --> 38:11.414
Uh, excuse me.
Could you leave this

38:11.414 --> 38:13.792
at the desk under
Tamara Colins? Thanks.

38:13.792 --> 38:15.502
Thanks.
Yeah.

38:15.502 --> 38:17.670
Hey, have you
ever been to the SCLA campus?

38:17.670 --> 38:19.672
I was there today,
and it is beautiful.

38:19.672 --> 38:21.466
You should check it out.
Yeah, right.

38:21.466 --> 38:24.177
I can't afford that.
They have scholarships.

38:24.177 --> 38:26.554
I could help you
apply for one.

38:26.554 --> 38:28.973
I don't know. Maybe.

38:28.973 --> 38:30.308
Well,
why don't you grab your stuff,

38:30.308 --> 38:32.227
and we can talk about it
over dinner?

38:32.227 --> 38:33.770
And then after that, I can drop
you at your cousin's house

38:33.770 --> 38:37.649
and see if "safe‐adjacent"
is safe enough.

38:37.649 --> 38:40.443
♪ Waiting there for me ♪

38:40.443 --> 38:43.655
[ Chuckles ]
♪ To come back home ♪

38:43.655 --> 38:44.739
Hi!

38:44.739 --> 38:46.199
♪ Come back home ♪

38:46.199 --> 38:49.577
Oh!
Aww, she's beautiful.

38:49.577 --> 38:55.792
♪ Back to these open arms
where you belong ♪

38:55.792 --> 38:59.671
♪ Come back home ♪

38:59.671 --> 39:01.047
[ Keys rattle ]

39:02.841 --> 39:04.467
[ <i>Ringing</i> ]

39:04.467 --> 39:05.635
♪ Is that you that I see
walking down the road? ♪

39:05.635 --> 39:07.053
Thanks for the gift.

39:07.053 --> 39:10.849
On the table
with the red bow.

39:10.849 --> 39:13.643
Then who did?

39:13.643 --> 39:14.936
I'll call you back.

39:14.936 --> 39:15.937
[ Cellphone beeps ]

39:15.937 --> 39:21.109
♪♪

39:21.109 --> 39:26.239
♪♪

39:26.239 --> 39:30.076
♪ Come back home ♪

39:30.076 --> 39:31.494
♪ Come back home ♪
De la Cruz: <i>"Querida Angela.</i>

39:31.494 --> 39:33.705
<i>In my country,</i>
<i>we tie a red ribbon</i>

39:33.705 --> 39:36.124
<i>around a baby's wrist</i>
<i>to ward off evil.</i>

39:36.124 --> 39:38.585
<i>Thank you for protecting</i>
<i>my child today.</i>

39:38.585 --> 39:41.379
<i>Consider this a gift of</i>
<i>protection for yours.</i>

39:41.379 --> 39:45.049
<i>Con cariño, La Fiera."</i>
♪ Come back home ♪

39:45.049 --> 39:49.804
♪ Come back home ♪

39:49.804 --> 39:56.644
♪ Back to these open arms
where you belong ♪

39:56.644 --> 39:58.771
♪ Come back home ♪

39:58.771 --> 40:00.231
[ Door closes ]
Don't worry.

40:00.231 --> 40:01.816
I'm giving you
exactly what you want.

40:01.816 --> 40:03.484
I'm leaving.

40:03.484 --> 40:07.614
If you were leaving,
you'd already be gone.

40:09.824 --> 40:11.951
You're waiting.

40:11.951 --> 40:13.536
Waiting for your audience
to appear

40:13.536 --> 40:15.747
so you can put on
another show.

40:15.747 --> 40:18.291
You think
that little of me?

40:18.291 --> 40:21.544
After everything I've done
for you, you hate me.

40:21.544 --> 40:23.588
Mom, I don't hate you.

40:23.588 --> 40:26.174
I'm just so tired
of playing the games.

40:26.174 --> 40:27.634
Aren't you?

40:27.634 --> 40:30.553
[ Zander Hawley's "Ever Yours"
plays ]

40:30.553 --> 40:32.597
Yes.

40:32.597 --> 40:36.517
♪♪

40:36.517 --> 40:41.230
Well, then, maybe we could try
not playing them

40:41.230 --> 40:43.691
and just be real
with each other.

40:43.691 --> 40:46.486
I don't know if you could
handle the real me.

40:46.486 --> 40:48.696
[ Both laugh ]

40:48.696 --> 40:52.075
But I'll give it a shot.

40:52.075 --> 40:55.119
Okay.

40:55.119 --> 40:58.623
How would you like me
to make a little supper?

40:58.623 --> 41:02.418
Unless you still
want me to leave?
Mom.

41:02.418 --> 41:03.962
Supper would be great.

41:05.880 --> 41:07.799
Okay.

41:07.799 --> 41:11.678
♪♪

41:11.678 --> 41:14.681
And the guest ro‐‐
That's my...

41:14.681 --> 41:16.057
♪♪

41:16.057 --> 41:20.979
♪ I put a lot on the line ♪

41:20.979 --> 41:23.856
[ Door opens ]
Luna: Hey.

41:23.856 --> 41:26.109
You were supposed to meet me
outside 15 minutes ago.

41:26.109 --> 41:27.860
[ Sighs ]

41:27.860 --> 41:29.737
I'm sorry. My bad.

41:29.737 --> 41:31.739
What happened?

41:31.739 --> 41:34.909
Wade. Talk to me.

41:34.909 --> 41:37.996
[ Sighs ]

41:37.996 --> 41:40.540
It's just...

41:40.540 --> 41:43.167
[ Sighs ]

41:43.167 --> 41:46.087
Percy's son
came to see me.

41:46.087 --> 41:48.756
His T. O.'s a problem.

41:48.756 --> 41:50.717
What kind of problem?

41:50.717 --> 41:52.677
You know what kind.

41:52.677 --> 41:57.473
♪♪

41:57.473 --> 41:59.767
When I joined the Department,
I told myself,

41:59.767 --> 42:02.145
"Do whatever you need to do
to survive,

42:02.145 --> 42:03.563
get a promotion,

42:03.563 --> 42:07.108
then you can make
some real change."

42:07.108 --> 42:09.777
And now
you're about to retire.

42:09.777 --> 42:12.071
And I haven't changed
a damn thing.

42:12.071 --> 42:14.657
Okay.

42:14.657 --> 42:18.786
Well, what you
gonna do about it?

42:18.786 --> 42:21.539
♪ Ooh ♪

42:25.918 --> 42:35.386
♪♪

42:35.386 --> 42:44.729
♪♪

42:44.729 --> 42:54.072
♪♪
